writer.close();
Pass true as the second argument in FileWriter constructor.

âœ… 10. What happens if you try to read a file that doesn't exist?
Java throws a FileNotFoundException, which is a checked exception.

You must handle it using try-catch, or declare throws IOException.

Example:

java
Copy
Edit
try {
    FileReader reader = new FileReader("nonexistent.txt");
} catch (FileNotFoundException e) {
    System.out.println("File not found!");
}
