Use File.listFiles() or File.list() to get all files in a folder.

âœ… 7. What is the difference between read() and readLine()?
Method	Description	Returns
read()	Reads one character at a time	int
readLine()	Reads one line at a time	String

read() is used for character-by-character reading.

readLine() is better for reading line-by-line.

âœ… 8. How to read all lines from a file into a List? (Java 8+)
java
Copy
Edit
import java.nio.file.Files;
import java.nio.file.Paths;
import java.util.List;

List<String> lines = Files.readAllLines(Paths.get("example.txt"));
for (String line : lines) {
    System.out.println(line);
}
Use Files.readAllLines() from java.nio.file package.

âœ… 9. How do you count the number of lines or characters in a file?
ðŸ”¹ Count Lines:
java
Copy
Edit
