âœ… 1. How to read and reverse each line using StringBuffer?
java
Copy
Edit
BufferedReader reader = new BufferedReader(new FileReader("example.txt"));
String line;
while ((line = reader.readLine()) != null) {
    StringBuffer sb = new StringBuffer(line);
    System.out.println(sb.reverse());
}
reader.close();
StringBuffer.reverse() reverses the content of each line.

âœ… 2. How to remove a specific line from a file?
java
Copy
Edit
BufferedReader reader = new BufferedReader(new FileReader("example.txt"));
List<String> lines = new ArrayList<>();
String lineToRemove = "MS Dhoni";
String line;
while ((line = reader.readLine()) != null) {
    if (!line.equals(lineToRemove)) {
        lines.add(line);
    }
}
reader.close();

BufferedWriter writer = new BufferedWriter(new FileWriter("example.txt"));
for (String l : lines) {
    writer.write(l);
    writer.newLine();
}
writer.close();
Reads all lines, skips the one you want to remove, and writes back the rest.

