âœ… 11. Whatâ€™s the use of mark() and reset() methods in BufferedReader?
mark(int limit) â†’ marks current position in stream.

reset() â†’ returns to the last marked position.

java
Copy
Edit
BufferedReader reader = new BufferedReader(new FileReader("example.txt"));
reader.mark(100);
System.out.println(reader.readLine());
reader.reset();  // Go back to previous mark
System.out.println(reader.readLine());
Useful for peeking ahead in streams without losing position.

âœ… 12. Explain how you would implement a log file system in Java.
