âœ… 13. How do you handle exceptions when working with files?
Use:

try-catch-finally

or better: try-with-resources (auto closes)

java
Copy
Edit
try (BufferedReader reader = new BufferedReader(new FileReader("example.txt"))) {
    // File reading
} catch (IOException e) {
    e.printStackTrace();
}